Definition: trade names of a narcotic analgesic that can be inhaled and that acts on the central nervous system and may become addictive
Example: used as a veterinary anesthetic and with other drugs before, during, and after surgery; also used as a nonlethal gas to incapacitate people in hostage situations; also abused as a recreational drug
Synonyms: Sublimaze, opiate, analgesic, trade, names, of, a, narcotic, that, can, be, inhaled, and, acts, on, the, central, nervous, system, may, become, addictive, used, as, veterinary, anesthetic, with, other, drugs, before, during, after, surgery, also, nonlethal, gas, to, incapacitate, people, in, hostage, situations, abused, recreational, drug
Category: noun.artifact
